parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ejection of a spark plug can cause engine damage, loss of power, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: Spark plug blows out of the cylinder head
loud bang or pop noise
engine stalling
loss of power
and damage to the engine and surrounding components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the CPS can cause the engine to shut down instantly, leading to a loss of power steering and brakes, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine stalling
loss of power
loss of power steering and brakes
intermittent stalling
and difficulty restarting the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the serpentine belt can cause a loss of power steering and brakes, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Sudden loss of power steering and brakes
engine stalling
and difficulty restarting the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tread separation and tire failure can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Tread separation
tire blowout
vibration
noise
bulges
and cracks in the tire sidewall.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Spare tire cable failure can cause the spare tire to fall off while driving, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Broken or frayed spare tire cable
spare tire falls off while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of brake lines can cause brake failure, leading to accidents or loss of control, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake pedal does not return to its normal position
brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to stop.
